It started innocently enough. Sarah Thompson, a former customer of CloudyApp Solutions, sent a straightforward email to support@cloudyapp.com:
&ldquo;Hi, I closed my account last week and would like to request that all my personal data be deleted from your systems. Thanks!&rdquo;
Unfortunately, this seemingly simple request opened a pandora&rsquo;s box of data governance and not only revealed what happens when software has not been designed with data governance in mind from the start, but rather than remove her personal details, cemented Sarah Thomas into the CloudyApp part of the internet for good.
